{
  "texts": [
    "The key-dependent variability in the frequency-domain representation does not substantially affect watermark distortion or detectability.",
    "In other words, given randomly selected watermark keys, the privacy-enhanced TAB-DRW should exhibit nearly consistent performance in terms of data fidelity and watermark detectability.",
    "From a theoretical perspective, since P κ is an orthogonal permutation matrix and the DFT/IDFT are unitary, inserting P κ before and P -1 κ after the frequency-domain transformation amounts to a norm-preserving change of entries in the original domain, meaning the total ℓ 2 distortion remains unchanged.",
    "Moreover, because detection evaluates sign alignment in the same keyed frequency coordinates, the resulting Z-score is invariant up to index relabeling.",
    "Empirical evidence supporting this claim is provided in Table is watermarked Table is not watermarked Pseudorandom Bits Generation Counting Statistics Watermark Embedding Watermark Detection Col."
  ]
}